==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cissoid
<hw>Cis"soid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ like ivy;
<?/ ivy + <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A
curve invented by Diocles, for the purpose of solving two celebrated
problems of the higher geometry; viz., to trisect a plane angle, and to
construct two geometrical means between two given straight
lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

